The '''2010 [[Gillette Fusion ProGlide 500]] Presented by Target''' was a [[NASCAR]] [[Sprint Cup Series]] motor race that was held on June 6, 2010 at [[Pocono Raceway]] in [[Long Pond, Pennsylvania]]. It was the fourteenth race of the [[2010 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series|2010 NASCAR Sprint Cup Series season]]. The event was scheduled to begin at 1 p.m. [[Eastern Daylight Time|EDT]] on [[Turner Network Television|TNT]], but it was delayed by rain to 3:00 p.m.<ref name=preview /> It was also broadcasted on the radio station [[Motor Racing Network]] at 12 p.m. EDT.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/|title=Sprint Cup Series Schedule|publisher=NASCAR|accessdate=27 March 2010}}</ref> The race consisted of 200 laps, 500 miles (804.67 km). 

The race began with [[Kyle Busch]], from [[Joe Gibbs Racing]], on the pole. During the race there were seven different leaders, fourteen lead changes, and eight cautions.<ref name=detail /> Then, [[Denny Hamlin]], also from Joe Gibbs Racing, won the 2010 Gillette Fusion ProGlide 500.<ref>{{cite web|title=Hamlin Wins 2010 Pocono Race|url=http://www.sportingnews.com/blog/unrestricted/entry/view/68178/denny_hamlin_wins_at_pocono_as_tempers_flare|publisher=Reid Spencer|accessdate=7 June 2010|location=[[Sporting News]].com|date=6 June 2010}}</ref>

== Race report ==
=== Practice and qualifying ===
[[File:Kyle Busch.jpg|thumb|left|200px|[[Pole position]] winner [[Kyle Busch]] in 2008.]]


Three practice sessions were scheduled before the race, one before qualifying on Friday, June 4, 2010, and two on Saturday, June 5, 2010.<ref>{{cite web|title=Pre-Race Schedule|url=http://www.poconoraceway.com/tickets_schedule_pocono_500.asp|accessdate=4 June 2010|location=[[Pocono Raceway]].com}}</ref> In the first practice session the quickest five drivers were [[Jimmie Johnson]], [[Juan Pablo Montoya]], [[Denny Hamlin]], [[Dale Earnhardt, Jr.]], and [[A. J. Allmendinger]].<ref>{{cite web|title=First Practice Results|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/14/data/practice1_speeds.html|accessdate=4 June 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> In the second practice, Jimmie Johnson was quickest, while Juan Pablo Montoya, [[Jeff Burton]], Clint Bowyer, and Kyle Busch followed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Practice 2 Results|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/14/data/practice2_speeds.html|accessdate=5 June 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> During the final practice session, Jeff Burton was first fastest, Jimmie Johnson second, Denny Hamlin in third, fourth is [[Jamie McMurray]], and Kevin Harvick fifth.<ref>{{cite web|title=Final Practice Results|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/14/data/practice3_speeds.html|accessdate=5 June 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref>

In qualifying, [[Kyle Busch]] won the [[pole position]], while [[Clint Bowyer]], Dale Earnhardt, Jr., [[Kurt Busch]], and Denny Hamlin completed the top-five positions.<ref name="qual">{{cite web|title=Race Lineup|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/14/data/lineup.html|accessdate=4 June 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> There were 45 entries for the race<ref>{{cite web|title=Qualifying Order|url=http://www.nascar.com/races/cup/2010/14/data/qual_order.html|location=NASCAR.com|accessdate=4 June 2010}}</ref>, but only 43 can race which meant that two drivers would not make the race; they were [[Terry Cook]] and [[Ted Musgrave]].<ref name=qual />

=== Race summary ===
At 12:00 p.m. EDT, Turner Network Television started broadcasting with the "Countdown to Green".<ref name="summary">{{cite web|title=Race Summary|url=http://www.nascar.com/2010/races/lapbylap/06/06/lap.by.lap.pocono/index.html|accessdate=6 June 2010|location=NASCAR.com}}</ref> At the start of the race, weather was predicted to be mostly cloudy with scattered thunderstorms. At 12:55 p.m. EDT, pre-race ceremonies began with  Mrs. Phil DeRea delivered the [[invocation]], then  Clarke Luis performed the [[U.S. National Anthem|national anthem]]. To start engines, the fans gave the command, "Gentleman Start Your Engines!". While under the pace laps, inclement weather moved in the area to cause a two hour rain delay. During the rain delay, NASCAR decided that there would be a competetion caution on lap 15.<ref name=summary />

At 3:07 p.m. EDT, the green flag waved to start the race. On lap 5, [[Denny Hamlin]] passed [[Kyle Busch]] for the lead. Ten laps later, the competetion caution came out, then most of the drivers came down to make their [[pit stop]]s . On lap 18, [[Bobby Labonte]] stayed out to lead one lap, then he came down to pit. Kyle Busch, on lap 20, led to field on the restart. Kyle Busch led the race until [[Clint Bowyer]] passed him on lap 38. Nine laps later, green flag pit stops began. On lap 79, Clint Bowyer pitted and gave the lead to Denny Hamlin, but two laps later, Bowyer regained the lead.<ref name=summary />  

On lap 85, there were only twenty-two cars on the lead lap where Clint Bowyer had lapped twenty-one cars. Twelve laps later, the second caution came out because of debris in turn two. Afterwards, all the lead lap cars pitted, and Kyle Busch regained the lead. On lap 101 the restart started with [[Kevin Harvick]], Kyle Busch, Denny Hamlin, Clint Bowyer, and [[Jimmie Johnson]] going four wide on the straightaway. Kevin Harvick then became the leader, but on lap 106, his car got loose and went toward the outside [[SAFER barrier|wall]] to give Denny Hamlin the lead. On lap 126, Denny Hamlin continued to lead with 75 lap to go. On lap 131, the second set of green flag pit stops began. One lap later, leader Denny Hamlin pitted, but kept his position on the race track.<ref name=summary /> 

On lap 151, the teams were worried because they didn't have enough to make it to the checkered flag. Four laps later, the third caution came out because there was debris on the Long Pond straightaway. After all lead lap car pitted, Denny Hamlin brought the field to the green flag, but on the same lap, the fourth caution came out because [[Casey Mears]], and [[Elliot Sadler]] collided. One lap later, Kyle Busch became the leader. On lap 164, the green flag waved as Kyle Busch was the leader. One lap later, Denny Hamlin regained the lead. On lap 167, [[David Ragan]] collided with [[Jamie McMurray]] to make him collide with the wall which brought out the fifth caution. Most of the leaders pitted for fuel, but [[Kurt Busch]] stayed out to become the leader on the restart on lap 171.<ref name=summary />

One lap later, [[Sam Hornish, Jr.]] passed Kurt Busch for the lead. On lap 175, the sixth caution came out because of debris in turn three. Some of the lead lap cars pitted, while the top-ten stayed out. Hornish, Jr, then, brought the field to the green flag on lap 179. Hornish continued to lead until Denny Hamlin passed him on lap 189. Ten laps later, the seventh caution came out because Kevin Harvick and [[Joey Logano]] collided. The caution caused a green-white-checkered finish; the restart was on lap 202. Then, one lap later, the white flag was given, but on the back stretch [[Kasey Kahne]] was blocked by [[A.J. Allmendinger]], then went through the grass, went toward the outside wall, went airborne as [[Mark Martin]] and [[Greg Biffle]] collided into him, and went to rest in the middle of the straightaway after [[Jeff Gordon]] collided head on with him. Then, Denny Hamlin took the checkered flag as he won his fourth race of the 2010 season.<ref name=summary />
